.F. |year=2007 |title=Neutral Ground: A Political History of Espionage Fiction |url= |publisher=Algora Publishing |isbn=0-87586-535-6}}\n* {{citation |title=Partial Payments |surname1=Epstein |given1=Joseph |publisher=[[W. W. Norton & Company]] |year=1991 |isbn=978-0-393-30716-0 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/partialpayments00jose }}\n* Venkataramiah, Munagala, 15 October 1938, ''Talks with Sri Ramana Maharshi''.\n* {{citation |surname1=Munagala |given1=Venkataramiah |year=1938 |title=Talks with Sri Ramana Maharshi |url=http://www.sriramanamaharshi.org |publisher=Sri Ramanashramam, Tiruvannamalai, Tamil Nadu, India |isbn=81-88018-07-4 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130828074451/http://www.sriramanamaharshi.org/ |archivedate=28 August 2013 }}\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Further reading==\n\n===Editions===\n* Burgess, Anthony (ed.) ''Maugham's Malaysian Stories'' (Hong Kong: Heinemann, 1969) [no ISBN]. Selected and introduced by [[Anthony Burgess]]. Includes ''The Vessel of Wrath'', ''The Force of Circumstance'', ''The Door of Opportunity'', ''The Four Dutchmen'', ''P. & O.'', and ''A Casual Affair''. Out of print.\n* Maugham, W. Somerset ''Collected Stories'' (London: Everyman's Library, 2004) {{ISBN|9781857152760}}.\n\n==External links==\n{{Library resources box}}\n{{commons category|William Somerset Maugham}}\n{{Wikiquote|William Somerset Maugham}}\n{{wikisource author}}\n* [http://www.caxtonclub.org/reading/smaugham.html Caxton Club Biography]\n* [http://www.britishempire.co.uk/biography/maugham.htm The British Empire, Biographies, Authors]\n* {{Gutenberg author | id=126 |name=Somerset Maugham}}\n* {{FadedPage|id=Maugham, W. Somerset (William Somerset)|name=W. Somerset (William Somerset) Maugham|author=yes}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=William Somerset Maugham}}\n* {{Librivox author|id=73}}\n* {{IMDb name|0560857|W. Somerset Maugham}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111117133221/http://www